# Patch Instruction

Because fixing npm vulnerabilities modifies `package-lock.json` and potentially `package.json`, which can be large and environment-dependent, a standard `.diff` file is not the best way to apply this patch.

Instead, maintainers should run the following command directly in the repository root:

```bash
npm audit fix
```

This will automatically update the dependencies and regenerate the `package-lock.json` file securely.